10px;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note:</strong><em> Money S=
tuff will be off for a few days tomorrow and early next week, back on Wedne=
sday.</em></p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Citrix</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A good trade is, you go to a bank and ask to b=
orrow a billion dollars, and the bank gives you the billion dollars, and th=
en the bank comes to you and says =E2=80=9Chey I just made this billion-dol=
lar loan to you, do you want to buy it,=E2=80=9D and you say =E2=80=9Csure =
I=E2=80=99ll pay you $836 million for it,=E2=80=9D and the bank says =E2=80=
=9Cugh fine I guess.=E2=80=9D And now you have borrowed $1 billion and paid=
 back $836 million and made a $164 million profit all at once. <a href=3D"h=
ttps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29137297.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3=
cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMjEvZWxsaW90dC1ib3VnaHQtM=
S1iaWxsaW9uLW9mLWNpdHJpeC1ib25kcy1ib29zdGluZy1pdHMtb3duLWJldD9jbXBpZD1CQkQw=
OTIyMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ=
1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA5MjImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cBa2b69062" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;">  Here you go</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elliott Investment Management bought about $1 =
billion of the junk-bond deal supporting its own buyout of software company=
 Citrix Systems Inc., according to people with knowledge of the matter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Paul Singer run firm was enticed by the st=
eep discount the banks that underwrote and distributed the Citrix financing=
 commitment offered on the debt, said the people, who asked not to be named=
 discussing a private transaction. The 6.5% secured bonds priced at 83.6 ce=
nts on the dollar Tuesday, bringing the all-in yield on the debt to around =
10%. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The decision helped support a transaction that=
 banks struggled to sell to investors for months. Wall Street banks underwr=
ote a $15 billion debt package in January to fund Vista Equity Partners and=
 Elliott=E2=80=99s buyout of Citrix. Since then, credit conditions have wor=
sened and borrowing costs have spiked, forcing the banks to absorb steep lo=
sses to offload the risk, and also sweeten the covenant package.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Firms led by Credit Suisse Group AG lost more =
than $500 million on the secured bond portion alone, Bloomberg reported.</p=
>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I mean it=E2=80=99s not=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</e=
m>good a trade. The reason Elliott and Vista are borrowing $15 billion is t=
o <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29137297.267530/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzg3Nzg5MC8wMDAxMTkzMTI=
1MjIwNzcyODMvZDIxOTEyMmRkZWZtMTRhLmh0bSN0b2MyMTkxMjJfNTU/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cBae36be3e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;"> buy Citrix for about $17 billion</a> in a deal th=
ey <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29137297.267530=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzg3Nzg5MC8wMDAxMTkzMT=
I1MjIwMjM0OTgvZDI3Mzg0M2RleDk5Mi5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd7ab108c" it=
emprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;"> signed in January</a> and expect to close at <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29137297.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvd=
i9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMDAwMDg3Nzg5MC8wMDAxMTkzMTI1MjIyNDg4=
MDMvZDQwMDk5OWQ4ay5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe6179fbb" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the end=
 of this month</a>. Before they signed,=C2=A0Citrix stock was trading in th=
e $80s, and they agreed to pay $104, a premium over the trading price. Afte=
r they signed, the stock market crashed, interest rates went up, and the sh=
ares of comparable software companies are down 20% to 45%. Elliott is proba=
bly not thrilled about owning Citrix at $104 per share, even if it got back=
 $164 million on the loan. (Plus, presumably the pocket of Elliott that is =
making the loan is different from the pocket of Elliott that is receiving i=
t.) Still if you can lend money to yourself and have some banks throw in so=
me extra money for free, that=E2=80=99s good.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The basic story of leveraged buyout debt is: I=
n a bull market, every week some private equity firm signs an agreement to =
do an LBO of some big public company. These deals have financing commitment=
s from banks, where the banks promise to lend the buyer the money to buy th=
e company at some maximum interest rate. But the deal won=E2=80=99t close f=
or several months while the company gets shareholder and regulatory approva=
l, and the banks don=E2=80=99t actually raise the money =E2=80=94=C2=A0sell=
ing bonds and loans to investors to fund their financing commitment =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0until shortly before closing. And so every week of the bull market=
 banks are making lots of lending commitments at bull-market rates. And the=
n one day the market turns, interest rates go up, and all the loans that ba=
nks agreed to make at last week=E2=80=99s rates turn out to be mispriced th=
is week. And then months later they actually go and sell those bonds and lo=
ans, in a bear market, at the interest rates they agreed to in their bull-m=
arket commitment letters. And they get, you know, 83.6 cents on the dollar.=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And they look kind of bad, but that is the nat=
ure of a cyclical business where you hold inventory for months. You could d=
o some hedging, both of interest rates and of broad high-yield credit.=C2=
=A0But ultimately if you are an investment bank you are in a competitive bu=
siness of servicing private equity firms, and if one of those firms is nego=
tiating a huge leveraged buyout it is generally good for your career to be =
a part of it. (Also the fees are=C2=A0good.) =E2=80=9CNo, we=E2=80=99ll sit=
 this loan out because we worry the market will turn in a few months=E2=80=
=9D is a tough position to take.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footno=
te-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !im=
portant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0=E2=80=9CAs long as the music is playing, you=E2=80=99ve got to g=
et up and dance,=E2=80=9D Citigroup Inc. Chief Executive Officer Chuck Prin=
ce famously said in 2007, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/29137297.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly9hcmNoaXZlLm55dGltZXMuY29tL2RlYWxib29rLm5=
5dGltZXMuY29tLzIwMTAvMDQvMDgvcHJpbmNlLWZpbmFsbHktZXhwbGFpbnMtaGlzLWRhbmNpbm=
ctY29tbWVudC8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB67e324b7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> about the LBO len=
ding business</a>, just before the music stopped.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway now everyone=E2=80=99s very unhappy abo=
ut Citrix, which looks like the turning point in the latest leveraged buyou=
t cycle. Bloomberg=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/29137297.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMjItMDktMjIvY2l0cml4LWRlYnQtZGViYWNsZS1oZXJhbGRzLWEtZGF5LW9mLXJlY2t=
vbmluZy1vbi13YWxsLXN0cmVldD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwOTIyMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaX=
VtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA5MjImdXRtX2NhbXBha=
WduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2c823221" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Davide Scig=
liuzzo writes</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Banks are nursing more than $600 million of lo=
sses on bonds and loans they just sold to investors at a steep discount. An=
d they=E2=80=99re sitting on about $6.5 billion more Citrix debt that they=
=E2=80=99ll be stuck with indefinitely.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It may be just the beginning. After the bigges=
t private-equity buyout boom in more than a decade, bankers still have to o=
ffload more than $50 billion in risky financing commitments, according to D=
eutsche Bank AG estimates. With central banks hiking interest rates to figh=
t inflation and recession angst intensifying, few investors want to touch t=
he debt without massive discounts, leaving the assets deeply underwater.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Major banks have already taken roughly $2 bill=
ion of writedowns this year. But those are now crystallizing into actual lo=
sses. The usually lucrative leveraged-finance business has all but dried up=
. Bonuses are being slashed. Job cuts may be next. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are other big financings in the market. =
Banks are trying to sell about $3.9 billion of debt for Apollo Global Manag=
ement Inc.=E2=80=99s acquisition of some internet assets from Lumen Technol=
ogies Inc. And two more deals are ahead: $8.35 billion of bonds and loans f=
or the buyout of TV ratings company Nielsen Holdings by Elliott Investment =
Management and Brookfield Asset Management, and $5.4 billion for auto parts=
 firm Tenneco Inc.=E2=80=99s buyout by Apollo.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I can think of one more! Roughly a quarter of =
the $50 billion of risky financing commitments that banks still have to sel=
l is the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29137297.=
267530/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAw=
MTEwNDY1OTIyMDQ5ODQ0L3RtMjIxMzE4OWQ4X2V4OTktaC5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB4f96267e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;"> $13 billion financing package</a> for Elon Musk=E2=80=
=99s buyout of Twitter Inc., which was agreed in April, when the market was=
 much better and when Musk <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/29137297.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMi8wNS8wNi90ZW=
Nobm9sb2d5L2Vsb24tbXVzay10d2l0dGVyLXBpdGNoLWRlY2suaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cB7c57948f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;"> had plans</a> to make Twitter profitable. Those l=
oans <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29137297.2675=
30/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDctMTEvbXVz=
ay1zLWRlYnQtYmFua2Vycy13b3VsZC1hdm9pZC1zdGVlcC1sb3NzZXMtaWYtZGVhbC1mYWxscy1=
hcGFydD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwOTIyMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3=
VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA5MjImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB12858dc3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">don=E2=80=99t look so good</a>=C2=
=A0now that rates are higher, the market is weaker and Musk is <a href=3D"h=
ttps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29137297.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3=
cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMTkvbWFya2V0LW1ha2luZ=
y1pcy1oYXJkLWZvci1ob3VzZXM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkyMjIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1=
bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwOTIyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWl=
nbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc86122aa" itemprop=3D"StoryLink"=
 itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  going around=
 saying</a> that Twitter is a fraud that =E2=80=9Cthreaten[s] U.S. national=
 security and democracy itself.=E2=80=9D If that financing prices at 85 cen=
ts on the dollar =E2=80=94=C2=A0comparable to Citrix, whose buyers=C2=A0<em=
>don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>think it=E2=80=99s a huge fraud<a class=3D"footnot=
e-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; =
display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0then that=E2=80=99s another $2 billion of losses for th=
e banks right there.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of course Elon Musk has told Twitter repeatedl=
y that he=E2=80=99s terminating that deal, and if he doesn=E2=80=99t actual=
ly buy Twitter then the banks don=E2=80=99t have to fund those loans. Twitt=
er has sued to force Musk to close, and I think the market views it as more=
 likely than not, though by no means certain, that Twitter will win. If you=
 are Morgan Stanley =E2=80=94=C2=A0Musk=E2=80=99s lead bank, on the hook fo=
r about 27% of the financing =E2=80=94=C2=A0how do you=C2=A0<em>account=C2=
=A0</em>for that commitment? Like when your quarter ends next week, do you =
take a $500 million writedown because you have a big debt commitment that i=
s underwater? Or do you say =E2=80=9Coh no this deal is canceled, no more c=
ommitment until we hear otherwise from a judge=E2=80=9D? Do you probability=
-weight it? If you are Musk=E2=80=99s coverage banker, and you take a non-z=
ero writedown, what is that conversation with Musk like? =E2=80=9CSorry yea=
h our accountants forced us to recognize that you=E2=80=99re going to lose=
=E2=80=9D?=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere here is the Wall Street Journal on <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29137297.267530/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9jaXRyaXgtZGVidC1kZWFsLXByaWNlcy13aXRoLW=
